  "position": 1,
  "is_published": true,
  "content_html": "<p>A <strong>complex number</strong> z = a + bi where a is the <em>real part</em>, b is the <em>imaginary part</em>, and i = √(−1).</p><h3>Basic Operations</h3><pre><code>(3+2i) + (1−i) = 4+i\n(3+2i) − (1−i) = 2+3i\n(3+2i)(1+i) = 3+3i+2i+2i² = 3+5i−2 = 1+5i\n</code></pre><h3>Complex Conjugate</h3><p>z̄ = a − bi. Key property: z × z̄ = a² + b² = |z|²</p><h3>Division</h3><pre><code>(3+2i)/(1+i) = (3+2i)(1−i) / (1+i)(1−i) = (5−i)/2 = 2.5−0.5i</code></pre><h3>Polar Form</h3><pre><code>z = r(cos θ + i sin θ) = r·e^(iθ)  (Euler's formula)\nr = |z| = √(a²+b²)  (modulus)\nθ = arg(z) = arctan(b/a)  (argument)</code></pre><h3>De Moivre's Theorem</h3><pre><code>z^n = r^n(cos(nθ) + i sin(nθ))</code></pre><h3>Euler's Formula</h3><pre><code>e^(iθ) = cos θ + i sin θ\ne^(iπ) + 1 = 0  (Euler's identity — most beautiful equation!)</code></pre>",
